<TITLE> Fire at Kazakhstan health clinic kills 38 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ALMATY, Sep 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A fire at a clinic for drug addicts in the southeastern Kazakh city of Taldykorgan killed 38 people on Sunday morning, the Central Asian state's government said. The Emergency Ministry said in a statement that workers evacuated and rescued another 40 people. The cause of the fire was unknown. "The fire was localised by 6:31 a.m. (local time)", the ministry said. The facility is one of many state-run healthcare institutions offering treatment and counseling to drug addicts in the former Soviet republic which lies on the main drug trafficking route from Afghanistan to Western Europe
